						<div class="postbody">Good news <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /> while looking for the answer and a possible solution to the problem I found this schematic on the web:<br /><br /><a href="http://arcadecontrols.com/images/stephan_snes_cc.gif" class="postlink">http://arcadecontrols.com/images/stephan_snes_cc.gif</a><br /><br />it caught my attention, that not used &quot;SI&quot; pin11 on the 2nd 4021 is not grounded there, so I tried it and un-grounded this pin in my circuit... and everything is working like a charm now! That did the trick.<br /><br />So... I guess (in mine experience) that unused serial data input on the 2nd 4021 <strong>should not be grounded</strong> ! Any idea why on almost every schematic on the web it is? Strange...</div>

